      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, just for regular updates (boot, system) it would be useful to have at least three slots (_a, _b, and _c).\n\nWhy? Because with only two slots you lose redundancy when as soon as you start the update... on ChromeOS this is a real problem because we stream the update payload (and support resuming an update in the middle)... so you can be in the situtation where you only have a single valid slot for a long time (until the update completes).\n\nOn current Android this is less of a concern but only because the entire update payload is downloaded in advance before starting the update process. This might change in the future especially as /system/update_engine (from ChromeOS) is used.\n\nSo, yes, there is real value in having at least three slots... but also, obviously, a real cost (moar disk space needed!). For now we support only two slots in AVB but we can easily change this in the future.",
